<Section classes={classes}>
	<Row>
		<Col>
			<h2>The API Gateway pattern at its full extent</h2>
			<p>
				KrakenD creates an API able to connect, secure, aggregate, transform or remove data from your services.
			</p>
			<h4><strong>KrakenD</strong> Key Features</h4>
			<p>Here’s a list of the main features of the KrakenD API Gateway</p>
			<ul class="list-group">
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>High Performance:</strong> KrakenD is designed for ultra-low latency and high throughput, making it ideal for handling large-scale traffic efficiently.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Flexible Architecture:</strong> Offers a fully customizable, declarative configuration to tailor your API gateway to your needs without writing additional code.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>No Middleware:</strong> A stateless architecture ensures there’s no dependency on external services, reducing complexity and improving reliability.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Advanced Caching:</strong> Built-in support for caching responses to reduce server load and improve client-side performance.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Authentication and Authorization:</strong> Provides features like OAuth, JWT, and more to secure your APIs out of the box.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Rate Limiting and Quotas:</strong> Protects your backend services by controlling traffic with rate limiting and usage quotas.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Service Composition:</strong> Allows combining multiple backend services into a single endpoint, reducing client complexity.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Built-In Security:</strong> Offers features like TLS termination, IP whitelisting, and more to protect your services.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Analytics and Monitoring:</strong> Provides integration with monitoring tools like Prometheus, Grafana, or ELK Stack for detailed insights.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Extensibility:</strong> Supports custom plugins written in Go for advanced customization and additional functionality.
				</li>
			  </ul>
			  
		  
			<h2><strong>KrakenD</strong>'s main use cases</h2>
			<p>
			  The reasons for KrakenD to be your strong option for your API Gateway:
			</p>
			<ul class="list-group">
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>API Gateway:</strong> Acts as a single entry point to your services, managing all API requests and responses efficiently.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Microservices Integration:</strong> Orchestrates multiple microservices into a cohesive API, reducing complexity for clients.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Backends for Frontends (BFF):</strong> Tailors APIs for specific client needs, enabling optimized and simplified API interactions for mobile, web, or IoT applications.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Load Balancing:</strong> Distributes requests across multiple backend services to improve performance and reliability.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Rate Limiting and Traffic Control:</strong> Protects backend services by managing request rates and controlling excessive traffic.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>API Security:</strong> Secures APIs with authentication (OAuth, JWT, etc.), IP whitelisting, and TLS termination.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Service Aggregation:</strong> Combines data from multiple services into a single API response, simplifying client-side logic.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Transformation and Filtering:</strong> Modifies, filters, or reformats API responses to suit client needs or comply with data privacy requirements.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>High Performance Caching:</strong> Reduces backend load and latency by caching frequently accessed responses.
				</li>
				<li class="list-group-item">
				  <strong>Monitoring and Analytics:</strong> Integrates with tools like Prometheus, ELK Stack, or Grafana to provide insights into API usage and performance.
				</li>
			  </ul>

			  {
				highlightBlocks.map((highlight, key) => (
					<TextImage
						id={`highlight-${key}`}
						title={highlight.title}
						text={highlight.text}
						image={highlight.image}
						imageWidth={highlight.imageWidth}
						imageHeight={highlight.imageHeight}
						mobileImage={highlight.mobileImage}
						imagePosition={highlight.imagePosition}
						classes={key === 0 ? '!pb-0' : key === highlightBlocks.length - 1 ? '!pt-0' : '!py-0'}
					/>
				))
			}
			  
		  

